oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Draft Board Selective Service Office
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of the interior of the Draft Board Selective Service Office for Tennessee in World War I. There are people sitting at desks.
The Draft Board Selective Service Office was in the building across from the War Memorial Auditorium, now the site of the Tennessee Tower.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Interiors; Offices; Draft (Military service); Military service
